This paper describes a neural network approach to ordinal regression, which is a type of learning that has properties of both classification and regression. The paper discusses the performance of the proposed method on several benchmark datasets and compares it with other methods such as Gaussian processes and support vector machines. The applications of the proposed method include information retrieval, web page ranking, collaborative filtering, and protein ranking in Bioinformatics. Based on these factors, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CV), information retrieval (cs.IR), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
